  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Ebola Virus Disease Operational Readiness and Preparedness in Burundi.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this WHO project is to enhance Burundi&#x2019;s capacity to efficiently prevent, early detect, and effectively manage the spread of an Ebola Virus Disease outbreak from DRC. With this CERF grant, WHO will supply 12 District Hospitals with kits and equipment to manage EVD cases and safe burials. WHO will also train 48 clinical staffs on EVD case management and infection prevention &amp; control. The project will last six months and will benefit 2,870,256 people including 1,460,960 women and girls and 1,409,296 men and boys.</narrative>
  </description>
